  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">arXiv</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">We performed a rough estimate of the non-perturbative value of the clover term coefficient cSW for the APE stout link Wilson fermion. We varied the number of smearings from Nsmear=1 to 6 and adopted beta values roughly corresponding to the lattice spacing of 0.1 fm. We used the Schroedinger functional technique for an evaluation of cSW and found that cSW decreases monotonically as we increase Nsmear but has a 10% order of deviation from the tree level value for Nsmear=6.</subfield>
  </datafield>
